                <title>Meritor Unitized Pinion Seal and Yoke Installation Instructions</title>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>To prevent serious eye injury, always wear safe eye protection when you perform vehicle
                            maintenance or service.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove old seal taking care to avoid damaging the bearing cage seal surface area. Do
                        not touch or allow dirt or grease to contaminate the sealing surface areas or the adjacent
                        bearings.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Inspect the bearing cage seal area for scratches, nicks or burrs that may promote
                        lubricant leakage after seal installation. Correct only minor damage using emery paper or
                        equivalent.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove the replacement unitized seal from package. Avoid particle contamination to
                        the seal surfaces. Handle the seal by the outside edges only. Take care and avoid touching the
                        inside area of the seal.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Select the proper seal driver for seal installation from table below. Each driver is
                        designed to properly install a specific diameter seal. To determine yoke seal diameter, measure
                        the yoke journal. See table below.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <para>The following table applies to these single models: RS-17-145, RS-19-145, RS-21-145, RS-21-160,
                    RS-23-160/A, RS-23-161/A, RS-25-160/A, RS-23-186, RS-26-185, and RS-30-185.
                </para>
                <para>The following table also applies to these tandem models: RT-34-145/P, RT-40-145/A /P, RT-44-145/P,
                    RT-40-160/A /P, RT-46-160/A /P, RT-46-164EH /P, RT-50-160/P, RT-52-185 (forward and rear input
                    only), and RT-58-185 (forward and rear input only).
                </para>
