                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position the driver and seal (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9914021">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <figure id="f9914021" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9914021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" resolution="300"/>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>On the forward tandem axle output position the R4422401 driver tool outer spokes or fins
                            MUST fit between the bearing cage bolts. Be sure that the bolts on bottom of bearing cage
                            are not in the path of driver spokes. If the driver spokes contact the bearing cage bolts,
                            the driver will not properly install the seal into the bearing cage seat and will also
                            result in damage to the driver. The reference mark on the driver tool should be in the 12
                            o'clock or the 6 o'clock positions when installing the new seal.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Do not use a hard head hammer to install seal. Use a soft head mallet. Using a hard head
                            hammer can damage the seal and driver tool.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Drive the seal into the bearing cage using a soft head mallet to seat the seal into
                        the bearing cage. The seal must be fully seated into or against the bearing cage (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9914022">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <figure id="f9914022" figsize="col-wide">
